lluminate the psychic motivations and gratifications underlying a range of contemporary cultural phenomena. These phenomena include nationalistic violence, the formation of normative masculinity, the psychic appeal of domination and submission, and the place of the "queer" desire in counterhegemonic practices. The contributors explore the role of psychoanalysis in shaping the future of cultural criticism; elaborate on innovative ways to approach group dynamics from a psychoanalytic perspective; rethink psychoanalytic understandings of authorship; and offer original interpretations of the intersections between gender, sexuality, and domination. Desire of the Analysts demonstrates that psychoanalysis remains an indispensable resource for critiquing our contemporary condition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh1 aForter, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForter, Greg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMiller, Paul Allen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Paul Allen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNell, Sharon Diane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSenasi, Deneen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilverman, Kaja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSussman, Henry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTorlasco, Domietta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZoberman, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 ažIžek, Slavoj, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part